<paragraph id="8BA136D1FFAB765BFC82D12E4994F091" blockId="118.[809,928,1398,1419]" box="[809,928,1398,1419]" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFC82D12E4994F091" box="[809,928,1398,1419]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FFAB765BFC82D1EC49E2F3BA" blockId="118.[809,1425,1460,1696]" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFC82D1EC4947F0D3" box="[809,883,1460,1481]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">Males:</emphasis>
This species can be recognized among congeners by the combination of the following features: the lack of prominent prosomal modification; the broad, apically pointed palpal tibial retrolateral apophysis without a tooth on the inner surface; lamella characteristica extal tip horn-like, with two projections, inner one triangular in ventral view, dorsal one blunt (fig. 5F in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B20FFAB765BFC82D2D349F2F3BA" author="Tu LH &amp; Li SQ" box="[809,966,1674,1696]" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" pagination="51 - 65" refId="ref96497" refString="Tu LH, Li SQ. 2006. A review of Gongylidioides spiders (Araneae: Linyphiidae: Erigoninae) from China. Revue Suisse de Zoologie 113: 51 - 65." type="journal article" year="2006">Tu &amp; Li, 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FFAB765BFC82D291495BF206" blockId="118.[809,1425,1737,1820]" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFC82D29149A0F3C4" box="[809,916,1737,1758]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">Females:</emphasis>
Can be diagnosed by the half-octagonshaped dorsal plate of the epigyne (figs 16, 
<quantity id="4CE69B34FFAB765BFABCD2B04F64F3E4" box="[1303,1360,1768,1790]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.318" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" unit="in" value="17.0">17 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B20FFAB765BFAFCD2B04954F206" author="Paik KY" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" pagination="153 - 173" refId="ref94012" refString="Paik KY. 1980. The spider fauna of Dae Heuksan-do Isl., So Heuksan-do Isl. and Hong-do Isl., Jeunlanam-do, Korea. Kyungpook Educational Forum Kyungpook National University 22: 153 - 173." type="journal article" year="1980">Paik, 1980</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FFAB765AFC82D31D48A7F717" blockId="118.[809,1369,1861,1883]" lastBlockId="119.[163,779,197,526]" lastPageId="119" lastPageNumber="536" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFC82D31D498FF240" box="[809,955,1861,1882]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F3097641FFAB765BFC6CD31D4E6DF241" box="[967,1113,1861,1883]" name="South Korea" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">South Korea</collectingCountry>
; 
<collectingCountry id="F3097641FFAB765BFBC8D31D4E9EF241" box="[1123,1194,1861,1883]" name="China" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49DAF833FFAB765BFB1DD31D4F61F241" box="[1206,1365,1861,1883]" country="China" name="Jilin" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">Jilin province</collectingRegion>
. 
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAA765AFF08D49D4B2DF5C0" box="[163,281,197,218]" italics="true" pageId="119" pageNumber="536">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B20FFAA765AFE99D49E4BC1F5C1" author="Tu LH &amp; Li SQ" box="[306,501,197,219]" pageId="119" pageNumber="536" pagination="51 - 65" refId="ref96497" refString="Tu LH, Li SQ. 2006. A review of Gongylidioides spiders (Araneae: Linyphiidae: Erigoninae) from China. Revue Suisse de Zoologie 113: 51 - 65." type="journal article" year="2006">Tu &amp; Li (2006)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B20FFAA765AFD96D49D48F7F5C1" author="Seo BK" box="[573,707,197,219]" pageId="119" pageNumber="536" pagination="35 - 39" refId="ref95179" refString="Seo BK. 2011. Two species of the genus Oedothorax from Korea (Araneae: Linyphiidae). Quantitative Bio-Science 30: 35 - 39." type="journal article" year="2011">Seo (2011)</bibRefCitation>
have provided informative drawings of three perspectives of the male palps of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAA765AFE25D55A48ECF40D" authorityName="Tu &amp; Li" authorityYear="2006" box="[398,728,258,279]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Gongylidioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="119" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kouqianensis">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAA765AFE25D55A48ECF40D" box="[398,728,258,279]" italics="true" pageId="119" pageNumber="536">Gongylidioides kouqianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAA765AFF08D5794B7CF42C" box="[163,328,289,310]" italics="true" pageId="119" pageNumber="536">
Oe. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAA765AFF7AD5794B7CF42C" authorityName="Seo" authorityYear="2011" box="[209,328,289,310]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="119" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insulanus">insulanus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, respectively, and their resemblance strongly suggests that these two species are identical. Since 
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAA765AFF5BD5074BAEF469" box="[240,410,350,372]" italics="true" pageId="119" pageNumber="536">
Oe. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAA765AFE8BD5064BAEF469" authorityName="Seo" authorityYear="2011" box="[288,410,350,371]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="119" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insulanus">insulanus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
was published earlier, it has priority over 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAA765AFE91D52548B7F488" authorityName="Tu &amp; Li" authorityYear="2006" box="[314,643,381,402]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Gongylidioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="119" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kouqianensis">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAA765AFE91D52548B7F488" box="[314,643,381,402]" italics="true" pageId="119" pageNumber="536">Gongylidioides kouqianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The palpal and epigynal morphology of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAA765AFE43D5C4493EF4AB" authorityName="Lin &amp; Lopardo &amp; Uhl" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="PAIK" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[488,778,412,433]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Gongylidioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="119" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insulanus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAA765AFE43D5C4493EF4AB" box="[488,778,412,433]" italics="true" pageId="119" pageNumber="536">Gongylidioides insulanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in accordance with the generic description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAA765AFF08D5814B60F4F4" authorityName="Oi" authorityYear="1960" box="[163,340,473,494]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Gongylidioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="119" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAA765AFF08D5814B60F4F4" box="[163,340,473,494]" italics="true" pageId="119" pageNumber="536">Gongylidioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B20FFAA765AFED6D582481BF4F5" author="Tu LH &amp; Li SQ" box="[381,559,473,495]" pageId="119" pageNumber="536" pagination="51 - 65" refId="ref96497" refString="Tu LH, Li SQ. 2006. A review of Gongylidioides spiders (Araneae: Linyphiidae: Erigoninae) from China. Revue Suisse de Zoologie 113: 51 - 65." type="journal article" year="2006">Tu &amp; Li (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, and supports the placement of this species in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAA765AFE49D5A048BFF717" authorityName="Oi" authorityYear="1960" box="[482,651,504,525]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Gongylidioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="119" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAA765AFE49D5A048BFF717" box="[482,651,504,525]" italics="true" pageId="119" pageNumber="536">Gongylidioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
